description:
Responsibilities :

Assist in managing all aspects of products being sourced and the actual production of those products to insure best pricing, quality, design, construction and timeliness;
Coordinate with factories to ensure on-time delivery;
Stay in daily contact with factories to manage work-in-progress report in real time;
Negotiate with manufacturers when needed;
Communicate production status to superior/US counterparts in a timely manner;
Provide analytical reports and maintain data up-to-date;
Requirements :

College graduate or equivalent;
A minimum of 4 years’ merchandising experience;
Good product knowledge of ladies handbags made from PU and fabric materials;
Hands on experience in handbags production management;
Experience in handling other fashion accessories such as belts will be an added advantage;
Strong organizational skills and attention to details;
Good written & spoken English, Cantonese & Mandarin

The role will be a member of our project team who is responsible for coordinating, optimizing and executing sourcing and sales related projects with co-effort from various departments.   

Key responsibilities:

Assist Director to handle sales and product development projects associated with the cosmetic bags product (Europe & US market);   
Carry out order management activity from quotation to invoicing and record progress in CRM (Salesforce) and ERP system;   
Source factory supplier via 1688 and other e-platforms, if necessary;   
Liaised with China factory and sub-contractor to ensure the production schedule and material delivery can meet the project requirement;   

 Requirements:

Minimum 2 – 3 years’ experience in cosmetic bag industry, less experience will be considered as Assistant Merchandiser;
Basic knowledge in fabric material and manufacturing know how of bags production;
Solid experience in sourcing factory supplier in 1688, etc;   
Good PC knowledge in using MS office applications;  
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);
New immigrants from Mainland are also welcome

We offer a friendly working environment near Kowloon Bay MTR with 5-day workweek, fringe benefits and incentive scheme. Interested candidates apply with full CV with work experience, current and expected salary.

Responsibilities:

Assist and support Merchandising Manager  in all matters relating to buying, operations, and promotion initiatives;
Regularly conduct market research; May attend overseas trade fairs with Merchandising Manager;
Monitor sales performance closely and execute stock transfer;
Perform relevant business analysis in order to develop appropriate action plans to achieve financial targets set by Company;
Work closely with Operations, Visual Merchandising team, and other counterparts to maximize sales performance of responsible category;
Conduct product training for the sales team.  

Requirements:

Degree holder preferably in fashion design or merchandising;
Minimum 2 years’ relevant working experience in high-end fashion;
Strong fashion sense, detail-oriented with good analytical and reporting skills;
Good team player with a strong sense of responsibility;
Excellent command of spoken English & Chinese;
Proficient in MS Word and Excel.

We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date available

by e-mail to: h r d  _ h n @ h a r v e y n i c h o l s . c o m . h k

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Position Objectives:

Managing full process of shipping. Providing routing information, issuing shipping instructions to ensure delivery is fulfilling the business window.


Job Descriptions:

Able to independently handle full set of Import/ Export document, purchase orders follow up with overseas and local suppliers;
Coordinate the inbound and outbound shipments with warehouse, internal departments, forwarders, and suppliers. It includes responding to customer or shippers’ daily operations and communications;
Monitor the shipment status, packing lists, reports, and system updates;
Liaise with account for the preparation of invoices;
Perform other ad-hoc tasks as assigned

Qualifications:

Form 7 or above with 4-5 years relevant experience;
Good command of written and spoken English, Mandarin and Cantonese;
Strong communication, negotiation, multi-tasking, and problem-solving skills;
Self-motivated, independent, good communication & interpersonal skill;
Able to work under pressure;
Excellent Microsoft Office skills (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)

Interested parties please apply with detailed resume with current & expected salary.

 Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.
